description:
Alchemy is a nanotechnology company based in Kitchener, Ontario with core operations in the automotive and defense sectors. 

Automotive - With the widespread adoption of ADAS systems in new vehicles, the cost of replacing a windshield in new vehicles has tripled to $1500+. We have developed a windshield protection film product line called ExoShield to help vehicle owners protect their windshields. Our ExoShield GT3 film is sold through 400+ aftermarket installers and car dealerships in 56 countries that carry and install it for vehicle owners. For Jeep Wrangler and Ford Bronco owners (google: broken windshield club), our ExoShield ULTRA DIY kits are available via our website and dropshipping partners. 

Defense - Over the last 3 years, we have been working with the Canadian Armed Forces to develop an infrared camouflage technology. We have received two contracts from CAF to develop our technology. Our solution has the ability to be integrated into the uniform directly (adding just 5-10g of weight vs. 600-18,000 kg of weight for other alternatives), has outperformed all existing NATO alternatives in multiple CAF field trials, and is receiving support from major elements of CAF for our next contract. This technology can also be adapted for other individual camouflage integrations (face paint and individual nettings) and for mobile camouflage applications (vehicle nettings and vehicle paints).

description:
Shopping? Buy overseas. 
Traveling? Earn some extra cash.
Let backpack help you save that high shipping cost or earn a little extra.

Backpack is a peer-to-peer platform that connects travelers and shoppers to give people access to products across markets in all continents. 
Each backpacker, regardless of their role as a carrier or a shopper, follows a simple four-step process to either earn or save money from their backpacking experience.
Travelers share their travel information and specify what kind of items they want to carry. Then they wait to get a "backpack request" and ask their price. Finally, they confirm the deal, buy the items, deliver them and earn money. Shoppers on the other hand, search items from their favorite websites and fill out the item description. Then they give their location and find a traveler coming to their city. Finally they "request backpack" and confirm the deal. Within days they can get the product and save money.  

backpack is founded with a vision to provide every citizen of the world with a choice; the choice of buying organic, authentic, and cost effective products with minimum friction.
Whether the product is state-of-the-art consumer electronics, exotic pashmina from the south-east, or even medication that are rare in some parts of the world and not so rare in others - we promise ourselves to get those products to your doorsteps. We would like to reject the counterfeits, we would like to reject the almost-originals, most importantly, we would like to not pay the heavy expense incurred, most of which we deem to be superfluous. Help us make a better, more original globalized world.
generated_description:
**Backpack: Simplifying Global Shopping**

Backpack is a fresh concept in the realm of e-commerce, designed to connect shoppers and travelers globally. Founded during the Y Combinator Batch S14 and based out of San Francisco, Backpack embarks on a mission to make international shopping more accessible and cost-effective. 

### What's the Idea?

If you've ever found yourself longing for a product available overseas but deterred by steep shipping costs, here's where Backpack comes in as a game changer. The platform facilitates a peer-to-peer marketplace where travelers earn by carrying items from one locale to another. It transforms the age-old notion of shipping into a community-driven model.

### How It Works

For **travelers**: You share your travel itinerary, indicate what items you'd be willing to carry, wait for a shopper's request, negotiate the price, and deliver the goods—all while earning some extra cash along the way.

For **shoppers**: You browse your favorite sites, submit item requests by filling out details, and then find a traveler headed your way. It’s a straightforward process designed to make cross-border shopping not just possible, but efficient. With just a few clicks, you save on shipping and gain access to products that might be scarce or overpriced in your own country.

### The Goals

Backpack aspires to empower everyone across the globe by giving them the choice to buy authentic and affordable products without the hassle of counterfeit goods and exorbitant shipping fees. It caters to diverse markets—from unique electronics to rare pashminas and even specialized medications—ensuring that everyone has a fair shot at the best the world has to offer.

### Why Choose Backpack?

- **100% Original Products**: Say goodbye to knock-offs—Backpack promises genuineness.
- **Easy Returns**: The user experience is seamless, including returns.
- **Global Reach**: Connect with travelers and shoppers worldwide, creating a bustling marketplace across continents.

In a nutshell, Backpack is about making the world a smaller place, enabling a better globalized market where high quality doesn’t have to come with high costs. Check them out at [backpackbang.com](http://backpackbang.com) and explore the possibilities of your next internationally-sourced purchase! 

With just two employees on the ground, the ambition is already global. If you have a wanderlust spirit and a knack for products that travel well, or if you're just keen to snag a deal internationally, Backpack is poised to revolutionize how we think about shopping across borders.
headline: Marketplace to get stuff from overseas
name: Backpack

generated_description:
**Greentoe: A Revolutionary E-Commerce Marketplace**

Founded in 2012 and part of Y Combinator’s S14 batch, Greentoe is redefining the traditional retail experience by putting the power of pricing back into the hands of consumers. Operating from New York City with a compact team of just five employees, Greentoe’s mission is simple yet innovative: "Name Your Price."

### The Concept

At its core, Greentoe operates as a next-generation e-commerce marketplace that allows shoppers to make offers on products they want. Instead of being at the mercy of retail prices, consumers can propose what they'd like to pay. The platform then connects these consumers with willing retailers who accept their offers, facilitating a win-win situation: shoppers get the best price possible while retailers can clear out inventory and attract new customers.

### Benefits for Everyone

- **For Consumers:** They receive products at potentially lower prices than standard retail offers.
- **For Retailers:** They can reduce excess inventory and broaden their customer base, making the platform attractive for both parties.

### Categories of Products

Greentoe features a wide variety of categories, including:

- **Photography Gear:** Cameras, lenses, drones, and accessories.
- **Home Entertainment:** TVs, sound systems, projectors, and headphones.
- **Appliances:** Kitchen and laundry appliances to meet everyday needs.
- **Baby Products:** Furniture, strollers, and safety gear.
- **Watches:** Fashionable timepieces and smartwatches.
- **Optics & Pro Video Equipment:** Scopes, binoculars, cinema cameras, and more.

Their website, [Greentoe.com](http://greentoe.com), showcases these products with enticing discounts and offers, encouraging users to engage.

### Consumer Engagement

Greentoe's platform not only allows for price negotiation but also emphasizes user engagement through features like “Greentoe Now,” which notifies users of real-time deals and discounts. This period of dynamic pricing adds to the allure, creating an engaging shopping experience where users feel in control.

### How It Works

For those curious about the mechanics of Greentoe, the process is straightforward:
1. **Browse Products:** Users explore different categories and select their desired items.
2. **Set Your Price:** The user proposes a price they are willing to pay.
3. **Offer Acceptance:** If a retailer accepts the offer, the user is notified and can complete the purchase.

### Mission Statement

Greentoe continually strives to empower consumers within the e-commerce landscape by offering transparency in pricing and value. They've built a marketplace that's not just about selling but about community and collaboration, often described as a refreshing shake-up in retail paradigms.

### Conclusion

Greentoe’s unique approach and focused mission provide a clear path for disruptive innovation in the e-commerce sector. By taking the traditional retail model and flipping it on its head, they make consumer participation a core part of the shopping experience—inviting everyone to partake in the value they seek while driving home the point that when it comes to buying, it's all about the price you set.

description: As third-party identifiers like the cookie disappear, ad-tech breaks—targeting, frequency capping and measurement disappear. generated_description:
### Permutive: Rebuilding Advertising Data with Privacy at Its Core

**Company Overview**
Permutive is a cutting-edge ad-tech company founded as part of Y Combinator's Batch S14. Based in London and currently employing 205 team members, it aims to revolutionize how data is used in advertising without compromising privacy. Dalton Caldwell serves as their Group Partner, and the company has carved a niche as a trusted solution for both publishers and advertisers. You can check them out at [permutive.com](https://permutive.com).

**Mission Statement**
At the heart of Permutive is a clear mission: to rebuild data in advertising in a way that protects user privacy. As third-party identifiers like the cookie wane, these issues require solutions that respect consumer rights while still making advertising effective.

**Core Proposition**
Instead of relying on traditional identifiers which are increasingly becoming obsolete, Permutive focuses on cohorts—privacy-safe groupings of users that allow advertisers to execute targeting and measurement strategies without needing to share personal identifiers. This innovative strategy moves data processing directly onto user devices, creating a more secure environment.

**What They Offer**
Permutive serves two primary audiences—publishers and advertisers—with tailored solutions:

- **For Publishers**: They provide comprehensive data collection and enrichment capabilities, enabling seamless activation across both direct and programmatic channels. This empowers premium publishers to scale their audience and optimize revenue.
  
- **For Advertisers**: The platform facilitates audience building, extending reach using first-party and partner data. The emphasis here is on achieving superior outcomes and accessing scalable, brand-safe inventory—all within a privacy-centric framework.

**Current Activities**
1. **Audience Scaling**: Helping publishers increase audience size, and advertisers extend their reach effectively.
2. **Data Collaboration**: Promoting a collaborative approach to data, allowing for richer engagement without compromising user information.
3. **Revenue Generation**: Focused on maximizing direct revenue for publishers and optimizing media spend for advertisers.

**Why It Matters**
Permutive’s approach is critical in today’s ad-space landscape, which faces increasing scrutiny around data privacy and security. By innovating the infrastructure needed for ethical advertising, they not only safeguard consumer data but also enable brands to reconnect with their audiences in meaningful ways.

In summary, Permutive isn’t just offering solutions; they’re championing a movement towards a sustainable ad-tech future that respects privacy, fosters collaboration, and ultimately drives better outcomes for all stakeholders involved.
headline: Rebuilding data in advertising to protect privacy
name: Permutive

description:
Protocol Labs is an open-source research, development, and deployment laboratory. Our projects include IPFS, Filecoin, libp2p, and many more. We aim to make human existence orders of magnitude better through technology.

Some of our projects.

IPFS makes the web work peer-to-peer. IPFS is a protocol for storing, addressing, and transferring data, designed to replace HTTP in many contexts. IPFS uses content-addressing to uniquely identify and link to information. IPFS is one of the leading protocols of Web3, crypto, and the decentralized web movements. IPFS serves millions of end users and tens of thousands of developers. It powers the websites and applications of small startups, large enterprises, and even blockchains.

Filecoin is a decentralized storage network, designed to store humanity's most important information. Filecoin is a cryptocurrency incentivized decentralized market, where storage providers earn filecoin tokens for renting out storage space. (Think airbnb for cloud storage). Filecoin is one of the leading projects in the cryptocurrency/blockchain space.
founders: [{'name': 'Juan Benet, Founder/CEO, Engineer', 'description': 'Juan founded Protocol Labs, IPFS, and Filecoin.', 'linkedin': 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/jbenetcs/'}]

Protocol Labs is driven by a bold mission: to create innovative internet protocols that fundamentally enhance how we interact with technology and each other. Founded in 2014 and hailing from Y Combinator's S14 batch, this Palo Alto-based company is a hub for open-source research, development, and deployment. With a growing team of 130, they are determined to make our lives better through groundbreaking advancements, particularly in the realms of decentralized computing.

At the heart of their offerings are two flagship projects: **IPFS** and **Filecoin**. 

**IPFS (InterPlanetary File System)** is a revolutionary protocol designed to make the web more peer-to-peer, intending to replace traditional HTTP in many scenarios. By utilizing content-addressing, IPFS allows users to uniquely identify and transfer data, making it an essential component of the rising Web3 and decentralized web landscapes. Today, IPFS supports millions of users and thousands of developers, powering applications across a spectrum of businesses from small startups to major enterprises and blockchains.

On the other hand, **Filecoin** serves as a decentralized storage network where users can securely store significant information. It’s akin to Airbnb but for data storage—users rent out their unused storage space in exchange for tokens. This incentivized model has positioned Filecoin as a leader in the blockchain situation, effectively creating a marketplace for data retention and accessibility.

Beyond these projects, Protocol Labs engages in various initiatives that span artificial intelligence, augmented and virtual reality, brain-computer interfaces, and hardware development. The company operates as an extensive innovation network, connecting over 600 startups, funds, accelerators, and open-source projects, thus facilitating collaboration and invention across multiple tech frontier sectors.

As a thought leader in digital human rights, Protocol Labs actively explores transformative ideas and revolutionary technology, striving to boost humanity's potential through computing breakthroughs.

If you want to dive deeper into their work, check out their website at [Protocol Labs](https://protocol.ai/), where you can learn more about their projects, blog articles, and opportunities to get involved. The company has rightly positioned itself within the B2B sales arena, offering benefits that include a measurable ROI—many of their clients have reported substantial increases in their pipelines and deal sizes since integrating UserGems into their workflows.
